CAPE TOWN - Howard Oliver has been found guilty for the rape and murder of Franziska Blochliger.On Tuesday, Oliver admitted to raping and killing the 16-year-old in the Tokai Forest in March 2016.Last year, the State prosecutor told the court that the Cape Town teen died due to suffocation, caused by sand being stuffed down her throat as well as pressing her face in the sand.The post-mortem report also indicated that the girl had been bludgeoned with a blunt object, the prosecutor said.Sentencing procedures continue at the Western Cape High Court on Thursday. eNCA